message: Many emperors were Illyrians such as Constantine the great and Justinian the great, the Illyrian language was spoken in the Eastern Roman Empire, so it is the right of the Albanians that the page of the Eastern Roman Empire on Wikipedia be written olso in Albanian. Who doesn't want it and takes the Albanian language off the page, This is called Racism and Discrimination. It is right to have the Albanian language on the page, that's why I want Wikipedia to keep it

According to sources such as historian Marin Mema and YouTube channel THESARI and other historians from different countries say that Stefan Dušan had people of Albanian origin in his family tree. Moreover, he refers to and affects Albanian history, so it is right that his name should also be written in the Albanian language.
